.Dd $Mdocdate: May 17 2026 $
.Dt CERTES.CONF 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm certes.conf
.Nd configuration file for certes
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
file configures
.Xr certes 8 ,
both in agent mode and in authority mode.
Some options apply only to one mode; these are noted below.
.Pp
The file is a flat list of
.Ar name No = Ar value
assignments, one per line.
Lines beginning with
.Sq #
are comments.
Booleans are
.Sy true
or
.Sy false ,
integers are unquoted decimal, strings are double-quoted, and string
lists are bracketed and whitespace-separated.
Durations are expressed in seconds unless the option name ends in
.Sy _ms ,
in which case they are in milliseconds.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Ss Common options
These apply to both agents and authorities.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic enable_coredumps Ar bool
Raise the core dump limit on startup.
Useful for debugging crashes; should be
.Sy false
in production.
Default:
.Sy false .
.It Ic authority_fqdn Ar string
For agents, the FQDN of the authority to contact.
For an authority, its own FQDN, which must match the CN in
.Ic cert_file .
.It Ic authority_port Ar uint
TCP port the authority listens on.
Default:
.Sy 9790 .
.It Ic agent_bootstrap_port Ar uint
Port the agent listens on for incoming dialback challenges during
bootstrap and renewal.
Default:
.Sy 9790 .
.It Ic root_cert_file Ar path
PEM file containing the root CA certificate used to validate peer
certificates.
Default:
.Pa ca.pem .
.It Ic cert_file Ar path
PEM file containing this host's certificate.
For agents, this is rewritten on each successful bootstrap or renewal,
so the path should live under a writable state directory such as
.Pa /var/lib/certes
on Debian or
.Pa /var/certes
elsewhere, not under
.Pa /etc .
On agents,
.Nm certes
and
.Xr mdrd 8
typically run as the same user, and the cert must be readable by both.
On authorities they usually run as separate users, each with its own
.Ic cert_file
and
.Ic key_file ;
the authority's signing cert lives in
.Pa /etc/certes
and is not rewritten at runtime.
Default:
.Pa cert.pem .
.It Ic key_file Ar path
PEM file containing this host's private key.
Created by
.Cm certes init
on agents and persists across renewals.
Same placement guidance as
.Ic cert_file :
agent keys live under a writable state directory, authority signing
keys under
.Pa /etc/certes .
Default:
.Pa key.pem .
.It Ic crl_path Ar path
Directory where CRLs are stored, one file per issuing authority named
.Pa <CN>.crl .
The directory is created with mode
.Sy 0755
if missing, so the CRLs are readable by other processes on the host.
Must be readable by both
.Nm certes
and
.Xr mdrd 8 ,
which consult it independently when verifying peer certificates.
.It Ic crl_reload_interval_seconds Ar uint
How often to poll the authority for updated CRLs.
Default:
.Sy 300 .
.It Ic lock_file Ar path
File used with
.Xr flock 2
to ensure only one
.Nm certes
process per host.
Default:
.Pa agent.lock .
.It Ic agent_socket_path Ar path
Unix-domain socket used by local administrative commands to
communicate with the running backend.
Default:
.Pa agent.sock .
.It Ic agent_send_timeout_ms Ar uint
Send timeout (milliseconds) for connections to the authority.
Default:
.Sy 60000 .
.It Ic agent_recv_timeout_ms Ar uint
Receive timeout (milliseconds) for connections to the authority.
Default:
.Sy 60000 .
.It Ic max_cert_size Ar uint
Upper bound (in bytes) on a DER-encoded certificate.
Used to size network buffers.
Default:
.Sy 4096 .
.It Ic roles_oid Ar string
OID for the
.Dq roles
X.509 extension.
All agents and authorities in the same deployment must agree on this
value.
Default:
.Sy 1.3.6.1.4.1.35910.3.1 .
.El
.Ss Agent options
These apply only when running as an agent.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic bootstrap_key Ar string
Base64-encoded one-time key obtained from
.Cm certes bootstrap-setup
on the authority.
Used on first startup to obtain a signed certificate.
Once bootstrap completes, the value is no longer consulted; it may be
left in the file or removed.
.It Ic cert_check_interval_seconds Ar uint
How often the agent checks whether its certificate needs renewal.
Default:
.Sy 600 .
.It Ic cert_min_lifetime_seconds Ar uint
If the current certificate's remaining lifetime drops below this,
the agent attempts renewal.
Default:
.Sy 345600
(4 days).
.It Ic challenge_timeout_seconds Ar uint
Time the agent will wait for a dialback challenge from the authority
during bootstrap or renewal.
Default:
.Sy 30 .
.El
.Ss Authority options
These apply only when running as an authority.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic cert_org Ar string
Organization (O) field used in the Subject DN of issued certificates.
.It Ic cert_email Ar string
emailAddress field used in the Subject DN of issued certificates.
.It Ic cert_renew_lifetime_seconds Ar uint
Lifetime assigned to a certificate when an agent renews it.
Default:
.Sy 864000
(10 days).
.It Ic cert_expired_retention_seconds Ar uint
How long expired certificate records are kept in the database after
their
.Sy not_after_sec ,
for forensic purposes.
Default:
.Sy 86400
(1 day).
.It Ic certdb_path Ar path
.Xr sqlite3 1
database storing issued certificates, bootstrap entries, and the
serial counter.
.It Ic certdb_backup_path Ar path
Destination for online backups of
.Ic certdb_path .
Backups are taken using SQLite's incremental backup API.
Leave empty to disable backups.
.It Ic certdb_backup_interval_seconds Ar uint
Frequency of online backups.
Set to
.Sy 0
to disable.
Default:
.Sy 86400 .
.It Ic certdb_backup_pages_per_step Ar uint
Number of pages copied per step of the incremental backup.
.Sy 0
or less means all remaining pages in one step (which blocks writers
for the duration of the backup).
Default:
.Sy 0 .
.It Ic min_serial Ar hex
.It Ic max_serial Ar hex
Inclusive range of serial numbers this authority may issue, given as
OpenSSL bignum hex strings starting with
.Sy 0x .
When running multiple authorities against the same population of
clients, assign each a non-overlapping range to avoid collisions.
.It Ic peer_authorities Ar list
List of FQDNs of peer authorities whose CRLs this authority should
fetch and serve.
For example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
peer_authorities = [ "auth2.example.com" "auth3.example.com" ]
.Ed
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/etc/certes/certes.conf"
.It Pa /etc/certes/certes.conf
Default location.
Overridden by the
.Fl config
flag or the
.Ev CERTES_CONF
environment variable.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
A minimal agent configuration:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
authority_fqdn = "auth.example.com"
authority_port = 9790
bootstrap_key  = "nL67iJsE/6dQRG+ZZYmgZm3bSyM22pSlO2UYMYLfxvxKpXELW3VfrZFrnPfbLPty"
root_cert_file = "/etc/certes/root.pem"
cert_file      = "/var/lib/certes/cert.pem"
key_file       = "/var/lib/certes/key.pem"
crl_path       = "/var/lib/certes/crls"
lock_file      = "/var/lib/certes/agent.lock"
agent_socket_path = "/var/lib/certes/agent.sock"
.Ed
.Pp
A minimal authority configuration:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
authority_fqdn = "auth.example.com"
authority_port = 9790
root_cert_file = "/etc/certes/root.pem"
cert_file      = "/etc/certes/ca_cert.pem"
key_file       = "/etc/certes/ca_key.pem"
crl_path       = "/var/certes/crls"
lock_file      = "/var/certes/agent.lock"
agent_socket_path = "/var/certes/agent.sock"

cert_org       = "Example"
cert_email     = "cert@example.com"
certdb_path    = "/var/certes/certdb.sqlite"
certdb_backup_path = "/var/certes/certdb.sqlite.bk"
certdb_backup_interval_seconds = 3600

min_serial     = "0x1000000"
max_serial     = "0x1ffffff"
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr openssl 1 ,
.Xr sqlite3 1 ,
.Xr certes 8 ,
.Xr mdrd 8
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Pascal Lalonde Aq Mt plalonde@overnet.ca
